      <h3 class="title">
      <a href="/article/7684#comment-12680" class="active">Re: SpinRite 6.0 for Linux Users</a>          </h3>
  
  
  <div class="picture">
  <img src="/files/linuxjournal.com/images/personicon.jpg" alt="Anonymous&#039;s picture" title="Anonymous&#039;s picture"  /></div>

  <div class="submitted">
    Submitted by Anonymous on Fri, 07/23/2004 - 01:00.  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <p>SpinRite 6.0 runs in DOS; if your RAID drives can be seen by DOS, then SpinRite can see them.  If you need a driver, you will need to find out if your RAID controller provides a DOS device driver.  If so, you can add it to the config.sys file on the SpinRite boot floppy.</p>
<p>Leon A. Goldstein</p>
      </div>

  
